 180 g), cut into quarters","1 garlic clove","2 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","2 sprigs fresh sage, leaves only","800 g canned chopped tomatoes","2 celeriacs, peeled and cut into 4 slices each (approx. 1.5 cm thickness)","160 g vegan cheese (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r341232","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-w1CYpwokDXE\/XZVQS9u9p6I\/AAAAAAAAc_c\/uF-58hNKXs8Iuxs5RIQ3EeyzibELZqeMACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_KFXBQRhG43Eg2xai.png","title":"Celeriac parmigiana","publishedAt":"2016-08-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"11.3 g","fat":"16.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"32 g","calories":"1496.4 kJ \/ 356.3 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, plate, shallow bowl, large plate, paper towel, large frying pan, oven, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["You can purchase flaxmeal at most major supermarkets, but to make your own, simply place 200 g flaxseeds into mixing bowl and mill <strong>30 sec\/speed 10<\/strong>. Transfer into a sealable container and store in the fridge or freezer for up to 3 months.","If you have leftover flaxmeal, you can use it as an egg substitute in baking. Combine 1 tablespoon flaxmeal with 30 g boiling water and set aside until it becomes jelly-like (equates to approx. 1 egg).","You can use any vegan cheese you like in this recipe. We used our Stretchy melty cheese (please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip)."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 10m","4 portions"]}